  "texts": [
    "The automation of knowledge curation and integration has significantly reduced the latency between knowledge creation and its application, improving decision-making processes across various domains [2,18].",
    "Furthermore, dynamic systems have introduced advanced methodologies for validating and verifying the accuracy of incoming data, thereby maintaining the integrity of the knowledge base, and the implementation of such systems demonstrated scalability and flexibility in handling diverse data types and sources, catering to the specific needs of different applications [5,11].",
    "Challenges related to data redundancy and inconsistency have been addressed through innovative deduplication and conflict resolution strategies, enhancing the quality of the information stored [19,20].",
    "Moreover, LLMs have facilitated a more personalized and context-aware information delivery, tailoring the knowledge presentation to fit the user's specific requirements and preferences [5,7].",
    "The adoption of dynamic knowledge management systems has paved the way for more sophisticated and intelligent applications, capable of responding to changes in their environment with a high degree of agility [21,22]."
